text.0: A 62-year-old man with chronic obstructive pulmonary disease came to the ED with 2 days of dyspnea. He was admitted to the ICU while in hypercapnic respiratory failure and placed on intubation and ventilation. Five days later, his urine became green. Which medication caused this?
text.1: The NEJM Clinical Cases Resource Center aggregates educational content and interactive cases to help medical professionals advance their clinical diagnostic and therapeutic skills and to provide engaging resources for teaching, continuous learning, and professional development.
text.2: Sonja Rasmussen, M.D., discusses guidance related to pursuing or delaying pregnancy during a public health emergency.  #COVID19 #SARSCoV2
